 two baking sheets with foil. Rub eggplant skin with olive oil, pierce the skin all over with a fork and place on prepared baking sheet. Roast for 25-30 minutes (450°F) until skin has charred and interior is fork tender. Once cooled (approx. 30 min.) peel eggplant and cut into pieces. Discard skin. Reduce oven to 350°F."},{"content":"Place dried mushrooms and water into mixing bowl and cook <b>6 min\/212°F\/\/speed 2<b>. Transfer to a heatproof bowl, cover with cling wrap and allow to rest 10 minutes. Strain mushrooms and reserve liquid. Dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place Parmesan into mixing bowl and grate <b>15 sec\/speed 10<b>."},{"content":"Add onion, garlic, parsley and basil and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Add reserved eggplant, reserved mushrooms, 2 tbsp reserved mushroom liquid, bread crumbs, egg and salt and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add pine nuts and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. Form 30 \"meatballs\" (approx. 1 oz. ea.) and place on prepared baking sheet. Bake for 30 minutes (350°F) or until golden brown. Keep warm while preparing sauce."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Hazelnut Romesco"},{"content":"Approximately 10 minutes before the \"meatballs\" are done, place hazelnuts and 0.5 oz Parmesan into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 6<b>."},{"content":"Add roasted red peppers, tomatoes, oil, garlic, parsley, 3 tbsp reserved mushroom liquid, water, vinegar, paprika, cayenne, salt and pepper and cook <b>6 min\/212°F\/speed 1<b>. Meanwhile, using a spiralizer prepare zucchini and carrot \"noodles\". Place Varoma into position and weigh in prepared carrots, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Carefully open Varoma lid away from you and weigh in prepared zucchini, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Transfer vegetables into bowls."},{"content":"Insert measuring cup into mixing bowl lid and purée sauce <b>1 min\/speed 3<b><strong>-8<\/strong> increasing speed gradually."},{"content":"Gently toss Eggplant \"Meatballs\" with Hazelnut Romesco and spoon over vegetable \"noodles\". Garnish with Parmesan and serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Garnish with hand-torn basil leaves or more pine nuts.","Eggplant is done when an inserted fork slides all the way in with no resistance."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","2h 45m","7 portions"]}